WEBVTT

00:09.240 --> 00:17.620
CHAPTERS XXI and XXII of the Book of Luke in the King James Version, also called the

00:17.620 --> 00:18.880
Authorized Version.

00:42.020 --> 00:47.260
CHAPTER XXI And he looked up and saw the rich men

00:47.260 --> 00:54.680
their gifts into the treasury. And he saw also a certain poor widow casting in thither two

00:54.680 --> 01:02.440
mites. And he said, Of a truth, I say unto you, that this poor widow hath cast in more

01:02.440 --> 01:08.680
than they all. For all these have of their abundance cast in unto the offerings of God,

01:09.320 --> 01:13.720
but she of her penury hath cast in all the living that she had.

01:15.040 --> 01:21.600
And as some spake of the temple, how it was adorned with goodly stones and gifts, he said,

01:22.600 --> 01:29.660
As for these things which ye behold, the days will come in which there shall not be left one

01:29.660 --> 01:37.140
stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down. And they asked him, saying, Master,

01:37.520 --> 01:43.640
but when shall these things be, and what sign will there be when these things shall come to

01:43.640 --> 01:52.600
pass? And he said, Take heed that ye be not deceived, for many shall come in my name,

01:52.840 --> 02:01.360
saying, I am Christ, and the time draweth near. Go ye not therefore after them. But when ye shall

02:01.360 --> 02:08.620
hear of wars and commotions, be not terrified. For these things must first come to pass,

02:08.620 --> 02:17.320
but the end is not by and by. Then said he unto them, Nation shall rise against Nation,

02:17.740 --> 02:23.100
and Kingdom against Kingdom. And great earthquakes shall be in diverse places,

02:23.700 --> 02:31.520
and famines, and pestilences. And fearful sights and great signs shall there be from heaven. But

02:31.520 --> 02:38.600
before all these they shall lay their hands on you and persecute you, delivering you up to the

02:38.600 --> 02:45.400
synagogues, and into prisons, being brought before kings and rulers for my name's sake.

02:46.240 --> 02:53.820
And it shall turn to you for a testimony. Settle it therefore in your hearts, not to meditate before

02:53.820 --> 03:00.860
what ye shall answer. For I will give you a mouth and wisdom, which all your adversaries shall not

03:00.860 --> 03:08.580
be able to gainsay nor resist. And ye shall be betrayed both by parents and brethren, and kinsfolk's

03:08.580 --> 03:15.760
and friends. And some of you shall they cause to be put to death. And ye shall be hated of all men

03:15.760 --> 03:23.980
for my name's sake. But there shall not an hair of your head perish. In your patience possess ye

03:23.980 --> 03:30.980
your souls. And when ye shall see Jerusalem compassed with armies, then know that the

03:30.980 --> 03:38.560
desolation thereof is nigh. Then let them which are in Judea flee to the mountains. And let

03:38.560 --> 03:45.180
them which are in the midst of it depart out. And let not them that are in the countries enter

03:45.180 --> 03:52.880
there into. For these be the days of vengeance, that all things which are written may be fulfilled.

03:53.980 --> 04:00.720
But woe unto them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days. For there

04:00.720 --> 04:07.520
shall be great distress in the land, and wrath upon this people. And they shall fall by the edge of

04:07.520 --> 04:14.860
sword, and shall be led away captive into all nations. And Jerusalem shall be trodden down of

04:14.860 --> 04:22.620
the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles be fulfilled. And there shall be signs in the sun,

04:22.860 --> 04:29.320
and in the moon, and in the stars, and upon the earth distress of nations with perplexity,

04:29.740 --> 04:36.280
the sea, and the waves roaring, men's hearts failing them for fear, and for looking after

04:36.280 --> 04:41.520
those things which are coming on the earth. For the powers of heaven shall be shaken.

04:42.360 --> 04:47.780
And then shall they see the Son of Man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.

04:48.600 --> 04:53.720
And when these things begin to come to pass, then look up and lift up your heads,

04:54.300 --> 05:00.140
for your redemption draweth nigh. And he spake to them a parable,

05:01.040 --> 05:08.160
Behold the fig tree and all the trees. When they now shoot forth, ye see and know of your own

05:08.160 --> 05:15.200
selves that summer is now nigh at hand. So likewise ye, when ye see these things come to pass,

05:15.600 --> 05:22.840
know ye that the kingdom of God is nigh at hand. Verily I say unto you, this generation shall not

05:22.840 --> 05:30.640
pass away till all be fulfilled. Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.

05:32.080 --> 05:38.520
And take heed to yourselves, lest at any time your hearts be overcharged with surfeiting

05:38.520 --> 05:45.340
and drunkenness and cares of this life, and so that day come upon you unawares.

05:45.980 --> 05:51.340
For as a snare shall it come on all them that dwell on the face of the whole earth.

05:51.900 --> 05:57.680
Watch ye therefore and pray always that ye may be accounted worthy to escape all these things

05:57.680 --> 06:04.300
that shall come to pass and to stand before the Son of Man. And in the daytime he was teaching

06:04.300 --> 06:11.300
in the temple, and at night he went out and abode in the mount that is called the Mount of Olives.

06:11.800 --> 06:17.460
And all the people came early in the morning to him in the temple for to hear him.

06:20.000 --> 06:21.360
Chapter 22

06:23.320 --> 06:28.040
Now the feast of unleavened bread drew nigh, which is called the Passover.

06:29.160 --> 06:34.900
And the chief priests and scribes sought how they might kill him, for they feared the people.

06:36.360 --> 06:42.640
Then entered Satan into Judas, surnamed Iscariot, being of the number of the twelve.

06:43.380 --> 06:50.400
And he went his way and communed with the chief priests and captains how he might betray him unto

06:50.400 --> 06:58.160
them. And they were glad and covenanted to give him money, and he promised and sought opportunity

06:58.160 --> 07:06.120
to betray him unto them in the absence of the multitude. Then came the day of unleavened bread,

07:06.120 --> 07:10.900
when the Passover must be killed. And he sent Peter and John, saying,

07:11.500 --> 07:15.100
Go and prepare us the Passover that we may eat.

07:16.600 --> 07:20.120
And they said unto him, Where wilt thou that we prepare?

07:20.860 --> 07:28.080
And he said unto them, Behold, when ye are entered into the city, there shall a man meet you,

07:28.200 --> 07:33.040
bearing a pitcher of water, follow him into the house where he entereth in.

07:33.680 --> 07:38.920
And ye shall say unto the goodman of the house, The master saith unto thee,

07:39.140 --> 07:44.320
Where is the guest chamber where I shall eat the Passover with my disciples?

07:44.880 --> 07:49.660
And he shall show you a large upper room furnished, there make ready.

07:51.100 --> 07:57.000
And they went and found as he had said unto them, and they made ready the Passover.

07:57.940 --> 08:03.860
And when the hour was come, he sat down, and the twelve apostles with him.

08:04.580 --> 08:12.220
And he said unto them, With desire I have desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer,

08:12.920 --> 08:20.560
for I say unto you, I will not any more eat thereof until it be fulfilled in the kingdom of God.

08:21.960 --> 08:30.320
And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and said, Take this and divide it among yourselves,

08:31.160 --> 08:38.120
for I say unto you, I will not drink of the fruit of the vine until the kingdom of God shall come.

08:39.800 --> 08:47.020
And he took bread, and gave thanks, and break it, and gave it unto them, saying,

08:47.980 --> 08:54.860
This is my body which is given for you, this do in remembrance of me.

08:56.480 --> 09:04.160
Likewise also the cup after supper, saying, This cup is the New Testament in my blood,

09:04.680 --> 09:12.560
which is shed for you. But behold, the hand of him that betrayeth me is with me on the table.

09:13.720 --> 09:20.900
And truly the son of man goeth as it was determined, but woe unto that man by whom he is betrayed.

09:22.120 --> 09:27.540
And they began to inquire among themselves which of them it was that should do this thing.

09:28.960 --> 09:34.020
And there was also a strife among them which of them should be accounted the greatest.

09:34.620 --> 09:42.540
And he said unto them, The kings of the Gentiles exercise lordship over them, and they that exercise

09:42.540 --> 09:51.440
authority upon them are called benefactors. But ye shall not be so, but he that is greatest among

09:51.440 --> 09:59.340
you, let him be as the younger, and he that is chief, as he that doth serve it. For whether

09:59.340 --> 10:06.540
is greater, he that sitteth at meat, or he that serveth, is not he that sitteth at meat,

10:06.540 --> 10:14.520
but I am among you as he that serveth. Ye are they which have continued with me

10:14.520 --> 10:21.640
in my temptations, and I appoint unto you a kingdom, as my father hath appointed unto me,

10:22.280 --> 10:27.820
that ye may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and sit on thrones judging the

10:28.250 --> 10:38.240
of Israel. And the Lord said, Simon, Simon, behold, Satan hath desired to have you,

10:38.420 --> 10:44.360
that he may sift you as wheat, but I have prayed for thee that thy faith fail not,

10:45.000 --> 10:48.080
and when thou art converted strengthen thy brethren.

10:50.160 --> 10:56.220
And he said unto him, Lord, I am ready to go with thee both into prison and to death.

10:57.160 --> 11:02.580
And he said, I tell thee, Peter, the cock shall not crow this day,

11:02.820 --> 11:06.740
before that thou shalt trice deny that thou knowest me.

11:08.040 --> 11:14.260
And he said unto them, When I sent you without purse and scrip and shoes,

11:14.920 --> 11:22.900
lacked ye anything? And they said, Nothing. Then said he unto them, But now he that hath a

11:22.900 --> 11:28.980
purse, let him take it, likewise his scrip, and he that hath no sword, let him sell his garment

11:28.980 --> 11:35.860
and buy one, for I say unto you, that this that is written must be yet accomplished in me.

11:36.340 --> 11:42.520
And he was reckoned among the transgressors, for the things concerning me have an end.

11:43.580 --> 11:50.540
And they said, Lord, behold, here are two swords. And he said unto them, It is enough.

11:51.640 --> 12:00.100
And he came out and went as he was wont to the Mount of Olives, and his disciples also followed

12:00.100 --> 12:08.180
him. And when he was at the place, he said unto them, Pray that ye enter not into temptation.

12:09.820 --> 12:17.180
And he was withdrawn from them about a stone's cast and kneeled down and prayed, saying,

12:17.740 --> 12:26.040
Father, if thou be willing, remove this cup from me, nevertheless not my will but thine be done.

12:27.540 --> 12:34.540
And there appeared an angel unto him from heaven, strengthening him. And being in an agony,

12:35.420 --> 12:42.960
he prayed more earnestly, and his sweat was as it were great drops of blood falling down to the

12:42.960 --> 12:51.000
ground. And when he rose up from prayer and was come to his disciples, he found them sleeping

12:51.000 --> 12:59.640
for sorrow. And said unto them, Why sleep ye, rise and pray, lest ye enter into temptation.

13:00.440 --> 13:07.320
And while he yet spake, behold, a multitude, and he that was called Judas, one of the twelve,

13:07.320 --> 13:15.120
went before them, and drew near unto Jesus to kiss him. But Jesus said unto him, Judas,

13:15.940 --> 13:23.420
betrayest thou the son of man with a kiss? When they which were about him saw what would follow,

13:23.740 --> 13:37.300
they said unto him, Lord, shall we smite with the sword? And one of them smote the servant of the

13:37.300 --> 13:46.060
fire. And he touched his ear, and healed him. Then Jesus said unto the chief priests,

13:46.260 --> 13:53.280
and captains of the temple, and elders which were come to him, Be ye come out as against a thief

13:53.280 --> 14:00.000
with swords and staves? When I was daily with you in the temple, ye stretched forth no hands against

14:00.000 --> 14:08.460
me. But this is your hour, and the hour of darkness. Then took they him, and led him,

14:08.800 --> 14:15.800
and brought him into the high priest's house. And Peter followed afar off. And when they had

14:15.800 --> 14:22.240
kindled a fire in the midst of the hall, and were set down together, Peter sat down among them.

14:23.440 --> 14:29.900
But a certain maid beheld him as he sat by the fire, and earnestly looked upon him, and said,

14:30.000 --> 14:37.200
This man was also with him. And he denied him, saying, Woman, I know him not.

14:38.940 --> 14:45.780
And after a little while another saw him, and said, Thou art also of them. And Peter said,

14:45.900 --> 14:54.740
Man, I am not. And about the space of one hour after, another confidently affirmed, saying,

14:55.280 --> 15:02.700
Of a truth this fellow also was with him, for he is a Galilean. And Peter said, Man,

15:02.700 --> 15:08.380
I know not what thou sayest. And immediately while he yet spake, the cock crow.

15:09.480 --> 15:14.880
And the Lord turned and looked upon Peter, and Peter remembered the word of the Lord,

15:15.340 --> 15:21.440
how he had said unto him, Before the cock crow thou shalt deny me thrice.

15:22.240 --> 15:30.620
And Peter went out, and wept bitterly. And the man that held Jesus mocked him,

15:30.760 --> 15:37.000
and smote him. And when they had blindfolded him, they struck him on the face, and asked him,

15:37.440 --> 15:45.040
saying, Prophesy, who is it that smote thee? And many other things blasphemously spake they

15:45.040 --> 15:51.860
against him. And as soon as it was day, the elders of the people and the chief priests

15:51.860 --> 15:59.740
and the scribes came together, and led him into their counsel, saying, Art thou the Christ? Tell

15:59.740 --> 16:10.100
us. And he said unto them, If I tell you, he will not believe. And if I also ask you, he will not

16:10.100 --> 16:17.440
answer me, nor let me go. Hereafter shall the Son of Man sit on the right hand of the power of God.

16:18.340 --> 16:26.040
Then said they all, Art thou then the Son of God? And he said unto them, Ye say that I am.

16:26.840 --> 16:33.000
And they said, What need we any further witness? For we ourselves have heard of his own mouth.

16:34.280 --> 16:41.580
End of chapter 22 of the Gospel According to St. Luke in the King James Version,

16:42.000 --> 16:44.300
also known as the Authorized Version.

